# General Safety Rules
- Only modify files I explicitly mention.
- Never touch test case output directories or anything matched by .cursorignore.
- Do not change numerics (schemes, physical constants, boundary conditions) unless I say so.
- Keep Fortran 90/95 module interfaces intact; avoid mass reformatting/rewrapping lines.
- If proposing refactors, present a short step-by-step PLAN first; wait for approval.
- After edits, show a concise DIFF per file and print the build command (`make`).

# Turbulence Model Safety Rules
- Preserve numerical stability in DNS/LES schemes.
- Do not modify FFT implementation without thorough testing.
- Maintain conservation properties in turbulence closures.
- Keep boundary condition treatments consistent in stretched grids.
- Test changes in both DNS and LES modes.
- Verify CFL conditions are properly maintained.

# Particle Tracking Safety Rules
- Preserve particle-flow coupling mechanisms.
- Maintain accuracy in Lagrangian particle tracking algorithms.
- Do not modify particle injection or removal logic without approval.
- Keep kdtree neighbor search optimizations intact.
- Verify mass/energy conservation in particle-flow interactions.
- Test particle tracking in both uniform and stretched grids.
- Preserve particle coalescence and evaporation physics.

# Test Case Safety Rules
- Test changes across multiple configurations (pi_chamber, channel, cfog).
- Maintain parameter file compatibility across all test cases.
- Preserve MATLAB postprocessing data formats.
- Do not modify established physical constants without explicit approval.
- Keep trajectory output formats compatible with visualization tools.